                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4737/35.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Chargé</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of Brazil</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-01-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 17, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>: Referring to the verbal
                    communication of this morning, it is now my painful duty to announce to you the
                    death of Mr. Joaquim Nabuco, the Brazilian ambassador, this morning at 11.40, of
                    cerebral hemorrhage.</p>
                <p>Be pleased to accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. L. Chermont.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
